Utterance.UttText: In room 10 is Jose Perera, 74 yrs old came in with Acute myocardial infarction (AMI).
He had history of previous MI three yrs ago and on antihypertensives.

Phrase.PhraseText: of previous MI three yrs ago

Utterance.UttText: He might have a third arrest.
So he is still needs to be on close monitoring, ongoing thrombolysis, ongoing ecg monitoring, obs, oxygen at 3 litres per nasal prongs.
Bloods came back positive and he is for full resus in the event of cardiac arrest.
GTN and morphine given and charted if he still need some more.
And for another set of bloods in the next 4 hours.
He had echo done showing 3 vessel blockage.
He hasn't given any consent yet.
